  "doc_id": "53812",
  "text": "Stem cells undergo discrete developmental changes throughout life but little is known about how these transitions are regulated. A particularly profound transition occurs between fetal development and adulthood, when stem cells from diverse tissues undergo changes in phenotype, function, and regulation [CITATION_1] . This raises the possibility that transcriptional programs that maintain stem cell identity and function change between fetal and adult life.",
